#MEM id=quality-of-earnings source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Finance/felix/skills/operating-system/quality-of-earnings/SKILL.md
M|quality-of-earnings|name: quality-of-earnings
M|quality-of-earnings|description: Distinguishes recurring vs. transactional revenue. Weights Hourbour MRR and Novizio revenue differently. Prevents consolidated reporting from overstating or understating financial health.
M|quality-of-earnings|version: 1.0.0
M|quality-of-earnings|Not all revenue is equal. A business with $10,000 MRR is fundamentally more valuable than one with $10,000 in one-time sales — because MRR compounds and the one-time sale must be re-acquired. Felix ne
M|quality-of-earnings|| Revenue Type | Source | Quality | Why |
M|quality-of-earnings||-------------|--------|---------|-----|
M|quality-of-earnings|| Subscription MRR | Hourbour | Highest | Recurring, predictable, compounding, sticky |
M|quality-of-earnings|| Expansion MRR | Hourbour | High | Existing customer growth — zero additional CAC |
M|quality-of-earnings|| Trial-to-paid conversion | Hourbour | Medium-High | pl signal — not yet recurring |
M|quality-of-earnings|| Repeat purchase revenue | Novizio | Medium | Customer loyalty, lower re-acquisition CAC |
M|quality-of-earnings|| New customer revenue | Novizio | Medium-Low | Transactional — requires full CAC to acquire again |
M|quality-of-earnings|| Product launch / promo spike | Novizio | Low | Seasonal, non-repeatable — flattering but not a trend |
M|quality-of-earnings|- Any consolidated YVON revenue report
M|quality-of-earnings|- Any month where Novizio has a product launch or promotional activity
M|quality-of-earnings|- Any comparison between Novizio and Hourbour financial performance
M|quality-of-earnings|- Investor updates (quality of earnings is what sophisticated investors actually assess)
M|quality-of-earnings|- Any report where MRR and transactional revenue appear in the same table
M|quality-of-earnings|Never add Hourbour MRR + Novizio revenue into a single line without first showing each separately with its quality label and composition.
M|quality-of-earnings|If Novizio revenue is elevated due to a launch or promotion, flag it as non-recurring and state baseline:
M|quality-of-earnings|"Novizio revenue this month: $18,000 (+40% MoM). Note: $6,000 is attributable to the SS26 launch — non-recurring. Baseline revenue ex-launch: $12,000 (+0% MoM trend)."
M|quality-of-earnings|When reporting consolidated YVON financial health:
M|quality-of-earnings|- Hourbour MRR growth is a stronger signal than Novizio revenue growth — state this explicitly
M|quality-of-earnings|- Hourbour NRR > 100% is a stronger health signal than Novizio repeat purchase improvement
M|quality-of-earnings|- Never present them as equivalent signals in an executive summary
M|quality-of-earnings|In investor updates: lead with Hourbour MRR (highest quality, most investable). Novizio follows as complementary revenue. Never present them as equivalent business lines without explaining the model d
M|quality-of-earnings|When a quality concern is present:
M|quality-of-earnings|```
M|quality-of-earnings|⚠️ Revenue quality note: $[X] of this month's reported revenue is [one-time / promotional / non-recurring]
M|quality-of-earnings|Baseline revenue (ex-[event]): $X
M|quality-of-earnings|Trend signal from baseline: [what the cleaned number actually tells us]
M|quality-of-earnings|```